community. I had jobs, got jobs that were rewarding and interesting, and I'm really happy

00:01:50.320 --> 00:01:58.080
with where my career has taken me since that time. I do, however, think that it's good to look back

00:01:58.080 --> 00:02:05.279
and kind of ask the question, why? Like, why did it go so badly? What about my own experiences and

00:02:05.279 --> 00:02:12.080
what the ecosystem was like led to me having such a rough experience? With the hindsight of 10 years

00:02:12.080 --> 00:02:17.839
and actually having come back and at least gotten moderately competent with Python in those

00:02:17.839 --> 00:02:24.000
intervening years, looking back, I think there's two things that together conspired to have me

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:30.559
